properties.label: Balsam Corner
properties.description: mountain on the Haywood-Swain county line. In Great Smoky Mountains National Park near lat. 35°40'17" N., long. 83°10'55" W., near a sharp bend in the county line, hence the name. Alt. 6,020.

properties.label: Coggins Branch
properties.description: rises in W Haywood County, Great Smoky Mountains National Park, near lat. 35°39'08" N., long. 83°06'12" W., and flows NE into Little Cataloochee Creek.

properties.label: Cooks Creek
properties.description: W Haywood County in Great Smoky Mountains National Park, rises near lat. 35°40'30" N., long. 83°09'38" W., and flows SE into Pretty Hollow Creek.

properties.label: Cooks Knob
properties.description: W Haywood County, Great Smoky Mountains National Park near lat. 35°39'28" N., long. 83°08'42" W., on Indian Ridge between Short Bung (ridge) and Davidson Branch.

properties.label: Correll Branch
properties.description: rises in W Haywood County, Great Smoky Mountains National Park, near lat. 35°42'05" N., long. 83°07'06" W., and flows SE into Little Cataloochee Creek. The stream has also been known as North Prong.

properties.label: Cosby Knob
properties.description: on the Haywood County, N.C.-Cocke County, Tenn., line, Great Smoky Mountains National Park, on the Great Smoky Mountains divide near lat. 35°43'47" N., long. 83°11'12" W. Alt. 5,145.

properties.label: Cove Creek Gap
properties.description: central Haywood County, Great Smoky Mountains National Park near lat. 35°37'52" N., long. 83°02'50" W., at the head of Winding Stair Branch. Alt. 4,071.

properties.label: Scottish Mountain
properties.description: W Haywood County in Great Smoky Mountains National Park near lat. 35°41'34" N., long. 83°05'08" W. Named for Scottish Mountain Lumber Co., which operated in the area in the 1920s. Alt. 4,290.
